    <title>Medgar Evers Home National Monument Act</title>
    <summaries>
      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <actionDate>2018-05-21</actionDate>
          <updateDate>2018-05-21T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Medgar Evers Home National Monument Act</b></p> <p>This bill establishes the Medgar Evers Home National Monument in Jackson, Mississippi, as a unit of the National Park System to preserve, protect, and interpret the resources associated with the pivotal role of Medgar Evers in the civil rights movement. </p> <p>The National Park Service shall enter into a cooperative agreement with Tougaloo College in Tougaloo, Mississippi, for interpretive and educational programming related to the monument and may enter into other cooperative agreements to carry out this bill. </p>]]></text>
